{{Shrine | Name = Aragami Shrine (荒神神社) | Image = [[File:Aragamishrine.jpg|250px]]{{Maplink2|zoom=12|frame=yes|plain=yes|frame-align=center|frame-width=280|frame-height=220|type=point|frame-latitude=39.3162|frame-longitude=141.5548}} | Location = {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県}}, {{ill|Tōno|ja|遠野市}}, Aozasa Town, Nakazawa 21-chome | Latitude_deg = 39 | Latitude_min = 18 | Latitude_sec = 11.1 | Longitude_deg = 141 | Longitude_min = 35 | Longitude_sec = 09.0 | Main_deity = {{ill|Gongen|ja|権現}} (Aragami-sama) | Shrine_rank = | Founded = Unknown | Main_hall = Hōgyō-zukuri, thatched roof | Other_names = | Pilgrimage_sites = | Annual_festival = | Rituals = | Map = Japan Iwate }}
'''Aragami Shrine''' (荒神神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in Nakazawa, Aozasa Town, {{ill|Tōno|ja|遠野市}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県}}.
Nestled in a narrow plot of land surrounded by fields, the shrine features a small {{ill|Hōgyō-zukuri|ja|宝形造}} structure with a thatched roof. From the site, visitors can see the distant {{ill|Mount Hayachine|ja|早池峰山}}, and the surrounding trees enhance its picturesque setting. The shrine is regarded as a symbol of Japan's rural charm, often described as part of the nation's {{ill|primal landscape|ja|原風景}}. It has been featured in various tourism posters and publications representing Tōno. In recognition of its cultural and scenic value, it was designated as Tōno Heritage Site No. 37 by the city.
== Main Deity ==
The shrine enshrines {{ill|Gongen|ja|権現}}, referred to locally as "Aragami-sama" (荒神様).
== History == {{Section stub}}
== Nearby Attractions == * {{ill|Denshōen|ja|伝承園}} – A folklore museum. * {{ill|Jōken-ji|ja|常堅寺}} – A Buddhist temple. ** {{ill|Kappa Buchi|ja|カッパ淵}} – A stream associated with kappa folklore.
== Related Topics == * {{ill|Tales of Tōno|ja|遠野物語}}
